A '''Survey Team''' was a unit of the [[Imperial Survey Corps/Legends|Imperial Survey Corps]] assigned to investigate [[Planet/Legends|planets]] and [[Moon/Legends|moons]] for the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. The standard procedure for an Imperial Survey Team when investigating an unknown world began by using orbital sensors to visually record the surface, scan for lifeforms, and take geological readings. If any sign of [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] life was found, no matter how low its level of technology, the team would land personnel on the surface to observe the natives up close.<ref name="GG">[[Galaxy Guide 5: Return of the Jedi (Second Edition)|''Galaxy Guide 5: Return of the Jedi'', Second Edition]]</ref>

Thousands of such teams searched for a suitable construction site for the [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]] and the [[Deflector shield generator/Legends|shield generator]] which would protect it during construction. [[IX3244-B]] under [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Toss]] was the team which discovered the [[Endor/Legends|forest moon of Endor]], the eventual construction site. IX3244-B's personnel consisted of both [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] and Imperial officers trained as scientists. They traveled from system to system on board a [[Survey Frigate]], and used [[Shuttle/Legends|shuttles]] to land on the planets or moons they investigated. Presumably, the spacecraft and personnel assigned to IX3244-B were typical of Imperial Survey Teams.<ref name="GG" />

